{"TopicId":173587,"ForumId":35,"TopicTitle":"[MAC] Launch Pad, a Mod Manager for macOS","CreatedByName":"breakthesystem","CreatedById":184409,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-07T12:31:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"breakthesystem","CreatedById":184409,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-07T12:31:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022launchpad.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022128\u0022 src=\u0022https://github.com/winsmith/launch-pad/raw/develop/docs/launchpad.gif\u0022 width=\u0022320\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cfont size=\u00224\u0022\u003ELaunch Pad is a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E Client written for macOS. It allows you to\u00A0download and install mods for Kerbal Space Program, including dependencies.\u00A0If you play KSP on a Mac, and find it hard to use the official \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E application using monodevelop, give Launch Pad a try!\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe app is \u003Cstrong\u003Estill being developed\u003C/strong\u003E, so while you can install most mods with it, you can\u0027t upgrade them right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe app uses the original \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E Metadata Repository, so all mods that are available on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E are also available in here.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d LOVE for some adventurous Mac users to try it out and leave feedback though.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/winsmith/launch-pad\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EMore Information on GitHub\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/winsmith/launch-pad/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDownload the latest Alpha Version\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/winsmith/launch-pad/issues\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESubmit Bugs and Feature Request\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore trying out Launch Pad, I\u0027d recommend creating a backup of your KSP directory, simply because it\u0027s still alpha software. If you have any question regarding how to install and use the app, please feel free to ask \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://github.com/winsmith/launch-pad/raw/develop/docs/screenshot.png\u0022 width=\u0022754\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-07T12:36:11Z\u0022 title=\u002204/07/2018 12:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 7, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by breakthesystem\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"salajander","CreatedById":72724,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-09T19:17:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNeat!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"breakthesystem","CreatedById":184409,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-10T08:21:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet me know if you try it out! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E Some parts are still rough around the edges, but making this awesome could be a lot of fun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ISE","CreatedById":161984,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-19T08:44:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have switched to windows a while ago, but I used to run \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E on mac OS X and know how hard it can be, very glad to see someone other there trying to make it better for the mac people! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"breakthesystem","CreatedById":184409,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-19T11:02:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! Right now I\u0027m working on supporting as much of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E spec as I can (because right now, some mods cant be installed yet) \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"batuchoux","CreatedById":196575,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-01T17:28:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t find my Steam folder when i use Launch Pad. How can i find it ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeltaDizzy","CreatedById":150755,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-01T22:28:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWoah! As a windows user, this almost makes me wish I had a Mac. Just the fact it gives you a picture is almost too much to handle by itself. It just makes normal \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E look so outdated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"breakthesystem","CreatedById":184409,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-03T10:05:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223573678\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221554139690\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196575\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022batuchoux\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/1/2019 at 7:28 PM, batuchoux said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t find my Steam folder when i use Launch Pad. How can i find it ?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI found \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zHbTfZ018OA\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis youtube video\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0about how to open your steam library in Finder. Once you have that, you can drag the folder from finder into the \u0022Open Folder\u0022 dialog from Launch Pad.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow this is a bit complicated, but macOS security principles make it hard to make this more user friendly (your Mac doesn\u0027t want any app to have access to the whole file system, so you have to pick a folder where it may play first)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223573905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221554157693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DeltaDizzy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/2/2019 at 12:28 AM, DeltaDizzy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWoah! As a windows user, this almost makes me wish I had a Mac. Just the fact it gives you a picture is almost too much to handle by itself. It just makes normal \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E look so outdated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot! \u0026lt;3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Marsu69","CreatedById":160048,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-07T08:10:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome !! Installing it right now ! Thanks a lot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teslamax","CreatedById":132175,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-16T21:32:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u00A0love your project!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t take the following too harshly. They\u0027re ideas/suggestions:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nI\u0027m using Mojave\u0027s dark mode so part of the color scheme changes, but not all. The result has a lot of contrast.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWould it be possible to scan the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s database to import the list of\u00A0installed mods?\u00A0I installed some using the stock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E command (GUI/command line/console UI) and don\u0027t want to have to do it again.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll stop by the GitHub repo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"breakthesystem","CreatedById":184409,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-22T18:47:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot for your GitHub issues! Oh yeah, Dark Mode is an awesome thing that I had on my list for ages.\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/winsmith/launch-pad/releases/tag/1a5\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ETadaaa!\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-04-22T19:19:27Z\u0022 title=\u002204/22/2019 07:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EApril 22, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by breakthesystem\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kylelander","CreatedById":207124,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-11T08:01:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis still works on Big Sur(11.0)!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kiki Tech","CreatedById":209978,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-10T17:47:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOSX 10.15 Catalina and Kerbal 1.11\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003ESome freeze (app not responding)\u00A0depending of the mod clicked on\u00A0the left bar.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-02-12T00:20:57Z\u0022 title=\u002202/12/2021 12:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 12, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Kiki Tech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gavel","CreatedById":215401,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-09-10T17:53:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there something that I am missing? I try to run this app and I get a screen with a progress bar that hangs up at about 30% and just \u201CBeeps\u201D and \u201CBops.\u201D No further progress even when left running for minutes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Smug_Space","CreatedById":233325,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-16T13:30:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it still work? You know, for the modern version of KSP? I am thinking of getting it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-16T13:49:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224380515\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221713274235\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022233325\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Smug_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Smug_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it still work? You know, for the modern version of KSP? I am thinking of getting it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod is for KSP1; all mods for KSP2 may be found in this area of the forum:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/130-ksp2-mod-releases/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/130-ksp2-mod-releases/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Smug_Space","CreatedById":233325,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-16T17:06:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224380522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173587\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221713275399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/16/2024 at 2:49 PM, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod is for KSP1; all mods for KSP2 may be found in this area of the forum:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/130-ksp2-mod-releases/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/130-ksp2-mod-releases/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still mean KSP1. Just the latest version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}